# v7sh-amd64: Licensing Notice

This project is a port of the original UNIX 7th Edition (V7) Bourne shell to x86_64 Linux.

## Original Code
The original source code of the V7 shell is the work of S. R. Bourne at Bell Telephone Laboratories. 
It was released by Caldera International, Inc. in 2002 under the Caldera Ancient Unix License (a permissive BSD-style license).

Original Copyright: 
Copyright (C) 2001-2002 Caldera International Inc. All rights reserved.
Copyright (c) Bell Telephone Laboratories / S. R. Bourne.

## x64 Port Modifications
The modifications and porting work to enable this shell to run on modern 64-bit Linux environments (including malloc-based memory management, stack refactoring, and 64-bit pointer fixes) were performed with the assistance of Gemini and Claude. These changes are licensed under the GNU General Public License version 2.

Port License: 
GNU General Public License version 2 (GPL-v2) or later.
See the [LICENSE](file:///home/mario/git/v7sh/LICENSE) file for the full text of the GPL-v2.

## Combined Work
The combined work is distributed under the terms of the GPL-v2, which is compatible with the permissive terms of the original Caldera/BSD license. All original attribution and copyright notices are preserved in the source files.
